subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. External morphology : Shell ( Figures 7I , 8I , 9I ) reduced, about 2.7 whorls, light orangebrown; protoconch sculptured with incised spiral grooves, otherwise shape and sculpture as for genus. Animal ( Figure 5E–F ) cream with red edge to foot and brown spots on side of foot; tiny specks of pale pigment present (similar pigment is iridescent in live specimens of
P. iridis
). Right mantle lap large, rounded; left mantle lap slightly smaller, tapering to a point; colour and fusion as for genus. Mantle lobes of medium size; left and median mantle lobes fused. Caudal horn moderately large.
